# Liabilities Other Financial Liabilities Repurchase Agreements Principal Amount

## identifier
de15159

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of the principal amount of cash borrowed (post haircut) on the initial leg of a repo transaction, which is a contractual arrangement involving the provision of securities or other financial assets (collateral) in exchange for cash with a commitment to repurchase the same or similar collateral at a fixed price either on a specified future date or on demand.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Liabilities.OtherFinancialLiabilities.RepurchaseAgreementsPrincipal.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo6.02.21
- period=instant
